race.description: Spelling At Coolmore Mt White Handicap (Bm72)
race.comment: STRAAND BEAUTY (1) showed great pace to lead then wouldn't lie down but was eventually swamped when resuming over this distance at Randwick on Boxing Day. Beaten less than a length on that occasion so there doesn't need to be great deal of improvement for him to be taking this out. DESTRUCTIVE DIVA (8) is racing well around the Capital and Riverina, the latest offering a fast-finishing third over today's journey in a BM65 at Canberra. Tougher here but she plummets in the weights and at a big price looks an appealing each-way bet. RUNRANIRUN (4) has led all the way for two easy victories from as many starts this prep, both over five furlongs. Needs to raise the bar now but a mare in form is worth following. SMILING PROPHET (6) has four top three finishes from as many runs at this trip, the latest a win when resuming in open company two back at Muswellbrook. Genuine contender. ACTION KING (3) hasn't won for a while but his record at 1000m is hard to knock.
